str2: A primary particle; but, and, etc.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Genitive Feminine Plural
str2: Any one, some one, a certain one or thing. An enclitic indefinite pronoun; some or any person or object.
A day, the period from sunrise to sunset.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Middle - Genitive Feminine Plural
str2: To pass (of time); I continue through, intervene. From dia and ginomai; to elapse meanwhile.
A king, ruler, but in some passages clearly to be translated: emperor. Probably from basis; a sovereign.
Agrippa, i.e. Herod Agrippa II. Apparently from agrios and hippos; wild-horse tamer; Agrippas, one of the Herods.
From a provincial form of phero and nike; victorious; Bernice, a member of the Herodian family.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural
str2: From kata and a derivative of anti; to meet against, i.e. Arrive at.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
From Kaisar; Caesaria, the name of two places in Palestine.

str2: To greet, salute, pay my respects to, welcome. To enfold in the arms, i.e. to salute, to welcome.
Festus. Of Latin derivation; festal; Phestus, a Roman.
